---
By: Maimonides
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 261
    Verse: 18
Tags:
  - Ignorance
---
An ignorant man believes the whole universe exists only for him. ... If,
therefore, anything happens to him contrary to his expectations, he at once
concludes that the whole universe is evil.
